### Test AgroScan API

### 1. Register a new user
POST http://localhost:5002/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "John",
  "lastName": "Doe",
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 2. Login with the registered user
POST http://localhost:5002/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 3. Create an inspection (replace {token} with actual JWT token from login response)
POST http://localhost:5002/api/inspections
Authorization: Bearer {token}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "plantName": "Tomato Plant",
  "inspectionDate": "2024-12-01T10:00:00Z",
  "country": "United States",
  "state": "California",
  "city": "Los Angeles",
  "notes": "Healthy plant with some minor leaf spots",
  "status": 0,
  "category": 1
}

### 4. Get user's inspections
GET http://localhost:5002/api/inspections
Authorization: Bearer {token}

### 5. Add an image to the inspection (replace {inspectionId} with actual inspection ID)
POST http://localhost:5002/api/inspectionimages
Authorization: Bearer {token}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "inspectionId": {inspectionId},
  "image": "https://example.com/plant-image.jpg"
}

### 6. Create an analysis for the inspection
POST http://localhost:5002/api/inspectionanalyses
Authorization: Bearer {token}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "inspectionId": {inspectionId},
  "status": 2,
  "confidenceScore": 0.85,
  "description": "Plant shows signs of early blight. Leaf spots are characteristic of fungal infection.",
  "treatmentRecommendation": "Apply fungicide spray every 7-10 days. Improve air circulation around plants."
}

### 7. Get latest analysis for inspection
GET http://localhost:5002/api/inspectionanalyses/inspection/{inspectionId}/latest
Authorization: Bearer {token}
